The audience at Mercedes Benz Fashion Week were surprised when a string of a list of celebrities walked the ramp for designer Stefenia Morland&#8217;s fashion show. They included Thuli Madonsela who is now based at Harvard University in Boston, US and Lindiwe Mazibuko who graduated with an MBA from the same university last year. They were followed by Boity, actress Kgomotso Christopher, rapper Yung Swiss, Thembi Seete and Top Billing presenter Ayanda Thabethe among other famous personalities. People who attended the show were also given t-shirts written &#8216;We should all be feminists&#8217;. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter